The simulation results of SRAM cells are demonstrated in this section with the emphasis on the performance characteristics of the proposed device (Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company) 1-Poly 6-Metals \(0.18\mathrm{-}\mu \mathrm{m}\) CMOS process. Fig.5 shows that the chip area is \(0.95\mathrm{mm}^2\) and the chip width is \(0.93\mathrm{mm}\) with correct operation. The chip area with pads is \(0.958^{*}8\) \(0.923\mathrm{mm}\) with 128bit including the peripheral circuits. The whole chip layout and the physical layout of the chip are shown in Fig.6, respectively. Table II shows that the manufacturing process, power supply voltage, power consumption and the duration tests are Writedelay, Writedelay, and Writedelay, respectively.<|txt_split|>For the read stability of SRAM, static noise margin (SNM) is the standard method to measure the read stability of a SRAM cell. It can be measured graphically from the butterfly graph. The butterfly graph is a plot of the read signal and the corresponding noise margin. Although, several definitions of the SNM can be found in the current textbooks, one standard SNM definition is not commonly used yet. According to [2], the SNM of a loadless SRAM cell as the diagonal of the rectangle with the read signal \( \mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{m}} \) and the read signal \( \mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{m}}^{\prime} \) and the noise margin low \( (\mathrm{NM}_{\mathrm{L}}) \), as shown in Fig.8, \( \mathrm{NM}_{\mathrm{L}} \) and \( \mathrm{NM}_{\mathrm{R}} \) are defined as Equations 1 and 2, respectively:<|txt_split|>\[
\mathrm {N M} _ {\mathrm {H}} = \mathrm {V} _ {\mathrm {O H}} - \mathrm {V} _ {\mathrm {B H}} \tag {1}
\]<|txt_split|>\[
\mathrm {N M} _ {\mathrm {L}} = \mathrm {V} _ {\text {I L}} - \mathrm {V} _ {\mathrm {O L}} \tag {2}
\]<|txt_split|>where \(V_{\mathrm{M}}\) is the maximum input voltage level recognized as logical 0, \(V_{\mathrm{M}}\) is the minimum input voltage level recognized as logical 1, and \(V_{\mathrm{M}}^{\prime}\) is the maximum logical 0 output voltage. \(V_{\mathrm{M}}^{\prime \prime}\) is the minimum logical 1 output voltage. The SNM expression can be presented as:<|txt_split|>\[
\mathrm {S N M} _ {\text {l o a d , l e s s S R A M}} = \sqrt {N M _ {\mathrm {H}} ^ {2} + N M _ {\mathrm {L}} ^ {2}} \tag {3}
\]<|txt_split|>Fig.9 and Fig.10 show the butterfly curves for the conventional 4T SRAM cell and 6T SRAM cell respectively. Fig.11 shows the butterfly curves for our proposed 7T SM cell, showing the operating environment at cell \(5\mathrm{V}\) and \(8\mathrm{V}\) rated frequency of \(25\mathrm{C}\), given Typical, Typical (TT) model. Our simulation results show that the read SNM of the proposed circuit is up to \(1.43\mathrm{V}\), while that of the conventional 4T and 6T SRAM cell is \(0.55\mathrm{V}\) and \(1.09\mathrm{V}\) respectively. Our design approach is based on the read SNM by 1.6X and 0.31X as compared to the conventional 4T SRAM cell and 6T SRAM cell respectively.
